'''The Mall Barnsley ''', also known by its original name the '''Alhambra Shopping Centre''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theretaildatabase.com/retail%20location.php?ID=78|title=The Mall Barnsley|publisher=The Retail Database|accessdate=2011-06-26}}</ref> is [[Barnsley]]'s main shopping complex, housing 41 shops and adjacent to Barnsley Market. The centre was opened in 1991. A number of chains have been in the centre in the past, most notable was [[Woolworths Group|Woolworths]] which ceased trading in December 2008. It was owned and operated by [[The Mall Company]], a large company that operates shopping centres throughout the UK until they sold it to TFC Reit in September 2011<ref>http://www.wearebarnsley.com/news-archive/breaking-news-the-mall-sold/ </ref>. In the centre there are a number of small retail stalls which encourage independent businesses to start.
Current stores (as of October 2010) include:
[[Primark]], [[TK Maxx]], [[Next (clothing)|Next]], [[Iceland (supermarket)|Iceland]], [[Vodafone]], [[Claires]] and [[Wilkinson (retailer)|Wilkinson]].
